<subSubSection pageNumber="279" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="279">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="279">Note:</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
, while clearly an 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Xanthorrhoeaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="279">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Aloë">Aloe</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, apparently cannot be identified to species. Wijnands (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="279">Bot. Commelins:</emphasis>
124. 1983) provided current names for each unnamed variety listed in the original description, as did Newton (in Eggli, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="279">Ill. Handb. Succ. Pl., Monocots:</emphasis>
133. 2001). The latter appears to treat this name as synonymous with 
<taxonomicName authority="Mill." authorityName="Mill." class="Liliopsida" family="Xanthorrhoeaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ferox">
